Graphic designer interested in the meaning 
of fantasy in relation to touch, art, and sense;
Roland dHerbemont is currently a student at
the Central Saint Martins School of Art and 
Design and investigating his own style through
mix media, 3D modeling and web design.

portsIn.value:
Note:

"RIDIA" is a mystical universe where premonitary signs
and symbolic dialectic is suppose to echoe an 
intimate interpretation of today's world.
In a series of 6 paintings curated into a space of
interaction, Roland d'Herbemont is giving a place for
his artwork to shine and begin a dialogue with the
spectator.
" I wanted everything to be focuse, silent and to be
as cohesive as possible for the viewer to forget 
his own body, own self. To become as free and as
sensitive one can be when he wakes up from a 
bad dream,...when his vision is still wobbly,
and in a certain way, prophetic I want to say."

    RIDIA Online Exhibition has been made possible
thanks to the support and use of the softwears
Cables gl and Github.com. Roland wanted to make
the code of his website open source and make it
a contribution to the world without taking any credit
on anything but the artistic direction.

  Enjoy!
